comments: Monk (SAC) dribbles the ball off of his own foot during the drive and Vincent (MIA) cleanly gathers the loose ball.
Huerter (SAC) is moving alongside Lowry's (MIA) path with his hand resting on Lowry's body as marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Huerter (SAC) legally contests Strus' (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) mutually engages with Lowry (MIA) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Sabonis disengages to release away toward the basket.
Adebayo (MIA) moves alongside Mitchell's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) is established in Adebayo's (MIA) path and rests his hand on Adebayo's body as he absorbs the marginal contact at the end of the drive.
Sabonis (SAC) jumps slightly toward Adebayo (MIA) as Adebayo spins away from the marginal contact in the lane.
Adebayo (MIA) and Barnes (SAC) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Vincent (MIA) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Sabonis (SAC).
Strus (MIA) removes his resting hand from Monk's (SAC) side at the start of his upward shooting motion and cleanly blocks the jump shot attempt.
Strus (MIA) blocks the shot and is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession correctly remains with the Kings.
During the inbound, Vincent (MIA) and Huerter (SAC) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the go over the screen.
Lowry (MIA) briefly grasps and immediately releases Barnes' (SAC) arm and marginal contact occurs as they engage off-ball.
Vincent (MIA) moves into and makes contact with Sabonis' (SAC) body, which affects his SQBR.
Adebayo (MIA) firms up in Mitchell's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Mitchell (SAC) rests a hand on Herro's (MIA) body and neither extends nor delivers contact during the play at the basket.
Sabonis (SAC) moves alongside of Herro's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs as his arm and Herro's off-arm come together during the play at the basket.
Herro (MIA) moves alongside of Mitchell's (SAC) path with a hand resting on Mitchell's body and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Barnes' (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Lowry (MIA) stops his forward momentum and release from the marginal contact with Sabonis (SAC) at the end of the drive.
Sabonis (SAC) legally contests Lowry's (MIA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Vincent (MIA) moves slightly toward Monk (SAC) and marginal body contact occurs as they come together, which Monk moves through to continue on his desired path to the basket.
Strus (MIA) and Adebayo (MIA) jump alongside Monk (SAC) and do not deliver contact during his pass attempt.
Strus (MIA) does not get ball height and initiates contact with Sabonis' (SAC) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Vincent (MIA) moves into Davis' (SAC) slightly extended arm to create the marginal contact during the inbound.

Davis (SAC) and Adebayo (MIA) mutually engage as they jostle for potential rebound position and marginal contact occurs as Adebayo loses his balance and stumbles to the ground. Adebayo falls into Davis and creates the incidental contact with Vincent (MIA).
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in Mitchell's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Vincent (MIA) establishes himself in Mitchell's (SAC) path and marginal contact occurs as they briefly engage on the switch after the pick.

Herro (MIA) ends his dribble by gathering in the air and landing on both feet (although his left lands slightly before his right). When he moves his right foot, he establishes his left foot as his pivot foot, which he then lifts and replaces to the floor before taking his jump shot.
Davis (SAC) legally contests Herro's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) abruptly and overtly extends into Adebayo (MIA) to initiate more than marginal contact, which affects his ability to defend the last second shot attempt.
Mitchell (SAC) briefly engages with Strus (MIA) and marginal contact occurs prior to Strus receiving the inbounds pass.
